metadata.name: Pages From A Redacted Document #44
metadata.description:
In a time of mistrust, fear and corruption this work looks to reflect how transparency and accountability are removed from those with responsibility with a simple black line.

An abstract representation of the murky world that lurks behind the corridors of power. Kept there hidden and away from the masses.  We demand more.

A representation of documents printed and hand written, that are augmented with highlighters and blocking out pens.

press 'S' to download the hi-res version, which will show the full detail.

metadata.name: FluxMongers #22
metadata.description:
FluxMongers are very old beings from another dimension and their spin produces huge amounts of energy and this energy discharge is what causes the realities of MAGNETIK to be distorted or even to be torn apart. Their ethereal nature, speed and might make their movements almost to be perceived as some kind of choreography but this can only be called a dance of destruction. What you are looking at is a frame frozen in their deadly dance…

FluxMongers were inspired by light paintings where the painter uses one or few sources of light to draw in the air very quickly and the drawing is captured by long exposure.

After going live,

- press ‘1’ to get a hi-res version and ‘2’ to get a medium-res version (hopefully it will work :/)

- press 's' to save a png

metadata.name: Elswhere #57
metadata.description:
Perlin noise walks into a Julia set and finds itself Elswhere. X is real, Y is imaginary, or is it the other way around? 

Elswhere is a unique generative art series in which noise and fractal math are combined to create whimsical shapes and motifs, with an infinite number of variations. Made with p5js.

For each pixel, the noise values corresponding to the X and Y coordinates are computed and then used as the real and imaginary components for initializing a Julia set recursion. The pixel is colored based on the number of steps it takes for the recursion to reach its base case.

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[2] Render 2000x3000px image.
[4] Render 4000x6000px image.
[6] Render 6000x9000px image.

Created by Elsif, 2022.05

metadata.name: Inertia #932
metadata.description:
This project will be reserved and free for 48 hours, for all the holders of any of my projects!

The amount of reserves for each user will be equal to the amount of all the token held at 13:00 CEST [UTC+2] (May 23)
(example: user holds 3 "Figment" and 2 "ACCUMULATOR", will be able to mint "Inertia" 5 times)

48h from now I will update the reserves list and burn the remaining tokens

WARINING: The reserves will expire 48h after the drop! And a price for the unlocked mintables will be set (unreserved mints will not be free).

---

"Inertia is a property of matter by which it continues in its existing state of rest or uniform motion in a straight line, unless that state is changed by an external force."

Particles are blasted from 2 to 4 sides of the canvas, each particle has its own mass and it has to traverse a friction-field, once it loses its momentum completely it stops and leaves a trace, adding or subtracting light from the canvas.

The friction-field has 18 possible mutation kinds.
Mutations are high-friction zones of various shapes.

Made just with JS on a canvas
right-click to save

metadata.name: Sherwood #396
metadata.description:
In the forest, foggy, cloudy weather creates a mysterious, otherworldly atmosphere.

----

Controls:
s or [double click] - save
1 through 8 - set the pixel density for higher resolutions. Base is 2000x1000.
d - increase debug level (none, overlay, overlay + animated drawing)
D - decrease debug level
[plus] or [equal] - increase the edition of the mint (see a new location with the same features)
[minus] - decrease the edition, to a minimum of zero

Made with:
- p5js
- Simplex noise (hills, cleared/forested, grass height, tree size & separation)
- Poisson disk sampling (tree distribution)

metadata.name: miniGlyph #95
metadata.description:
In celebration of #tezos4tezos I am releasing this mini version of a more complex work in progress. 

Every 24th mint (ex: 1, 24, 48, 72, etc) will receive a free physical woodcut.
https://alleditions.art/p/miniglyph

This project is designed such that it can export a layered vector SVG that can be used for plotting or cutting out of wood with a laser or paper with a Cricut.

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers
